Document: ResourceImporterLayeredTexture
Path: godot/classes/class_resourceimporterlayeredtexture.rst
Summary: Describes the import properties for layered textures, focusing on compression and mipmap generation.

Property Descriptions
compress/channel_pack (int) = 0
Controls how color channels should be used in the imported texture.
Options:
- sRGB Friendly: Prevents R and RG color formats, which don't support nonlinear sRGB encoding.
- Optimized: Allows RG format if the texture doesn't use the blue channel, reducing memory if the blue value is always 0.
- Normal Map (RG Channels): Forces RG format, preserving only red and green channels. This is effective with VRAM Compressed or Basis Universal compression modes and only applies to Cubemap, CubemapArray, Texture2DArray, and Texture3D.

compress/hdr_compression (int) = 1
Controls VRAM compression for HDR images.
Options:
- Disabled: Never uses VRAM compression for HDR textures. Converts to RGBE9995 to reduce memory.
- Opaque Only: Uses VRAM compression only for opaque HDR textures due to limitations with transparent HDR formats.
- Always: Forces VRAM compression even for HDR textures with an alpha channel, discarding the alpha channel on import.
Note: Only effective on Radiance HDR (.hdr) and OpenEXR (.exr) images.

compress/high_quality (bool) = false
If true, uses BPTC compression on desktop (BC7 for SDR, BC6H for HDR) and ASTC on mobile.
If false, uses faster but lower-quality S3TC on desktop (DXT1 for opaque, DXT5 for transparent/normal maps) and ETC2 on mobile/web.
BPTC and ASTC support HDR compression, while S3TC and ETC2 do not.

compress/lossy_quality (float) = 0.7
The quality setting for the Lossy compression mode. Higher values mean better quality but larger file sizes on disk. This does not affect memory usage.

compress/mode (int) = 1
The compression mode to use, offering different tradeoffs between quality, memory usage, disk size, and import speed.
Options:
- Lossless: Original quality, high memory/disk usage, fast import.
- Lossy: Reduced quality, high memory usage, low disk size, fast import.
- VRAM Compressed: Reduced quality, low memory/disk usage, slow import. Recommended for 3D scenes only.
- VRAM Uncompressed: Original quality, high memory usage, highest disk size, fastest import.
- Basis Universal: Reduced quality, low memory/disk usage, lowest disk size, slow import. Recommended for 3D scenes only.

compress/rdo_quality_loss (float) = 0.0
Enables Rate-Distortion Optimization (RDO) if greater than or equal to 0.01, reducing file size at the cost of quality. Enabling RDO significantly increases encoding times.

compress/uastc_level (int) = 0
The UASTC encoding level. Higher values improve quality but increase encoding times.

mipmaps/generate (bool) = true
If true, generates smaller versions of the texture on import. This prevents pixelation at a distance in 3D or when scaled down in 2D, and improves performance by using smaller textures. The downside is increased memory usage (approx. 33% for Texture2DArray, Cubemap, CubemapArray; 14% for Texture3D). Recommended for 3D, optional for 2D based on visual benefit.

mipmaps/limit (int) = -1
Unimplemented. This property currently has no effect.

slices/arrangement (int) = 1
Controls the internal layout of a cubemap's texture. Options like 2x3 and 3x2 are less likely to exceed hardware texture size limits for high-resolution cubemaps compared to 1x6 and 6x1.